  "raw_html": "<button type='button' role='link' class='btn btn-link p-0 text-start' id='link_2' aria-label=\" Ghanshyam Soni versus State (Govt. of NCT of Delhi) & Anr. pdf\"  class='noToken' href='#' onclick=javascript:open_pdf('2','2025','2025_7_331_345','2025INSC803'); ><font size='4'> <strong>GHANSHYAM SONI<span class='fst-italic'> versus </span>STATE (GOVT. OF NCT OF DELHI) & ANR. </strong>- <span class='escrText'>[2025] 7 S.C.R. 331</span><span class='ncDisplay'>2025 INSC 803</span><input type='hidden' id='cnr' value=ESCR010002752025></button></font><br><strong>Coram : B.V. NAGARATHNA<sup style=\"color: #268e97;font-size: 22px;top: 0;\" class=\"tooltip-sup\" data-tooltip=\"Author\">*</sup>, SATISH CHANDRA SHARMA</strong><br> Issue for Consideration Issue arose whether the cognizance on the complaint u/ss.498A rw s.34 IPC was taken beyond the limitation period as mandated u/s.468 CrPC; and whether the prima facie case u/ss.498A rw s.34 IPC was made out against the appellant-husband or his family. Headnotes&dagger; 1973 &ndash; s.468 &ndash; Penal Code, 1860 &ndash; ss.498A, 34 &ndash; Bar to taking cognizance after lapse of the period of limitation &ndash; Allegations of cruelty and dowry demand against the appellant-husband and in-laws, by the respondent no.2-wife &ndash; Both parties police officer<br><strong class='caseDetailsTD' ><span style='color:#212F3D' > Decision Date :</span><font color='green'> 04-06-2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Case No :</span><font color='green'> CRIMINAL APPEAL No. 2894/2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Disposal Nature :</span><font color='green'> Appeal(s) allowed</font>   <span style='color:#212F3D' > |  Bench :</span><font color='green'> 2 Judges</font></strong><div class='row my-1 mt-2 border bg-light'><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclick=open_splitview('2','2025','2025_7_331_345','2025INSC803','S')><i <i class='fas fa-columns me-2'></i>Split view</a></